    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then roughly chop the <strong>spring onions</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways then slice diagonally into half-moons</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the\u00a0<strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces then add to a bowl with\u00a0the\u00a0<strong>cornflour\u00a0</strong>and and give\u00a0everything a good mix up until the\u00a0chicken\u00a0is fully coated</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>coated\u00a0chicken thigh pieces</strong>\u00a0and the <strong>soy sauce</strong> to the pan\u00a0and cook for 4-5 min on each side until the chicken has started to brown and crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is lightly browned, add the <strong>carrot half-moons</strong>\u00a0and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>spring onion</strong> (save the rest for later!)\u00a0and cook for 2-3 min until softened</p><p>Once the carrot and\u00a0spring onion have softened, reduce the heat to medium, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong> and <strong>cashew nuts</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>\u00a0and 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>water\u00a0</strong>to the pan, give everything a good mix up and cook for 2-3 min until thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Add another splash of water if it's looking a little thick!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>remaining spring onion </strong>\u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>Chinese\u00a0cashew chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-cashew-chicken-and-basmati-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Chinese\u00a0cashew chicken</strong> over the <strong>cooked basmati rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
